    Class Description
    addAppointment
    This class handles all the functions of the add appointment screen
    addCustomer
    This class handles all the controls for the addCustomer screen
    Appointment
    This class allows for the creation of a new appointment object in a Observable List which then can be added to the database
    appointmentDB
    This class handles getting the appointments from the database, deleting them, creating them, as well as modifying them
    Customer
    This class allows for the creation of new Customer objects inside of a observable list.
    customerDB
    This class handles the majority of database functions for the Customers table
    defaultZoneId
    LAMBDA interface that is needed for the lambda in the login controller
    fill
    LAMBDA Interface that is needed in order to use fill lambdas
    JDBC
    This class handles opening and closing the connection to the database
    Login
    This class handles all functions of the Login Screen including getting the users location, default language, and opens the connection to the database
    Main
    This is the main class of the application, it starts up the initial screen
    mainMenu
    This class is the controller for the Main Menu screen it handles switching between the various screens as well as displaying a majority of the data
    modifyAppointment
    This class handles the modify appointment screen
    modifyCustomer
    This class handles all controls for the modify customer screen
    reports
    This class is the controller for the reports screen which shows 3 seperate reports.
